					<h2 style="color: white">A telemarketer recognizes a voice.</h2>
					<h3 class="smallertitle" style="color: grey">I looked down at my feet, I looked at the bright blue socks I was wearing, I looked up at Jim's face and failed to hold eye contact, I looked around his cube and the numerous coffee stains on the desk and the carpet, and finally, looked back at him. "I've got nothing to lose, man. I'll be polite and frank and if I'm lucky she won't be creeped-out. I'll simply ask her out for coffee. If I fail, I fail. So it goes."
						The next day, my heart was pounding. I did the research the previous night and found absolutely nothing. My stalker-powers were thwarted. And so, I dialed her number. It's just a phone call. I didn't talk to Jim first; I didn't need a pep-talk. The phone rang, I could feel my heartbeat through my ear as it pressed against the phone, the ring tone came, and then went, came, and went, came, went -
						"Hello? This is -"
						It was her voice.
					</h3>
