				<h2 style="color: white">It begins with a toaster.</h2>
				<h3 class="smallertitle" style="color: grey">A jarring CLAP shakes old man Avery from his early-afternoon daydream. The noise came from the sound of the toaster's spring launching a crispy, golden-brown bagel into the air. It was a sound that he hated: he always loved the bagel the toaster produced, but he cursed under his breath every time the contraption ejected the food with a sound not entirely unlike that of a car crash. He is so startled that as he rises from his small, wooden table in the corner of the kitchen, he can't recall the daydream that was occupying his uneventful afternoon. He moves across the kitchen and reaches for the bagel but is interrupted by a knock at the door. He leaves the bagel in the toaster and moves toward the door. A man with a clever smile and combed, blonde hair is standing on the porch. The man has a small amount of perspiration on his tanned and handsomely wrinkled forehead, and he carries a coat upon his left shoulder. His sleeves are rolled up, and he says with a smile, "Hello, Mr. Avery. You've never met me, but I'm the God of All Things. I have a request for you." Avery blinks and shakes his head in confusion. "That's an odd introduction. Well, what's your request?" The man who claims to be God melts into a warm smile, "We'll talk about that, but let's step inside, it's unbearable out here."
				</h3>
